item.title: Episode 233: A FEAST FOR CROWS, BRIENNE I: "The Knight Errant"
item.description: Hello and welcome to the NotACast, the one true chapter-by-chapter podcast going through A Song of Ice and Fire! In this episode, Brienne of Tarth, truest of NotAKnights, sets out to find a princess who will always, always be in another castle. Next time: we're taking next week off, but the week after that, we'll be covering AFFC, Samwell I, in which Sam is ready to take on the Others, but maybe not a mouse. Poor little guy (meaning both Sam and the mouse). Emmett's twitter: twitter... Feed: https://notacastasoiaf.podbean.com/feed.xml

item.title: The reality stopping water pipelines to the parched western US
item.description: With so much water in the eastern U.S., why can't the region pipe some of it to its drought-prone neighbors in the West? This perennial question nags climate journalists and western water managers alike. We break down why building a pipeline is unrealistic right now for the Colorado River... Feed: https://feeds.npr.org/510325/podcast.xml
